OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 4 Apr to Mon 13 AprFIt
OL,6,Fis increasingly likely that unsettled
OL,7,Fconditions will affect the UK over the
OL,8,FEaster Holiday weekend, with the
OL,9,Fpotential for strong winds and heavy
OL,10,Frain at times. The wettest and
OL,11,Fwindiest weather is more likely
OL,12,Ftowards the west and north of the
OL,13,Fcountry. Beyond Easter, a broad
OL,14,Fnorthwest-southeast split is most
OL,15,Flikely, though the extent of high
OL,16,Fpressure into southern areas is
OL,17,Funclear. That said, northern and
OL,18,Fwestern parts are more likely to
OL,19,Fremain rather unsettled overall, with
OL,20,Ffurther spells of wind and rain, and
OL,21,Fareas further southeast should see the
OL,22,Fbest of the drier, clearer interludes.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,FTemperatures probably fairly close to
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Faverage overall, but occasional warmer
OL,25,Fspells are possible in the south.
